The foundational execution layer of the crypto ecosystem.
Layer 1 and Layer 2 networks provide scalability, security, and throughput, enabling mass adoption and high-volume on-chain activity. Layer 2s, in particular, are gaining strong momentum due to ecosystem expansion and reduced transaction costs.

